Below is the **complete system-level design and procedural framework** for:

# üî∑ LOGIC 8 ‚Äì Evaluation Framework & Scoring Logic

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ PURPOSE OF THIS LOGIC

This logic ensures that:

* Bids are evaluated using predefined criteria (from Logic 3)
* Scoring is objective and structured
* Comparisons are transparent and reproducible
* Decisions are defensible in audits or legal challenges
* Bias and arbitrary judgment are minimized

If this logic is weak ‚Üí awards become vulnerable to dispute, corruption allegations, and reputational damage.

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ CORE PRINCIPLES

‚úî Criteria defined and locked before publication (Logic 3)
‚úî Scoring aligned with envelope model (Logic 6 & 7)
‚úî Separation of duties (Logic 2 RBAC)
‚úî Audit trail for every score
‚úî Weighted mathematical aggregation
‚úî Justification mandatory for non-automated scoring

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ HIGH-LEVEL EVALUATION FLOW

```
Technical Envelope Opened (Logic 7)
        ‚Üì
Evaluator Assignment Confirmed
        ‚Üì
Individual Scoring Phase
        ‚Üì
Score Submission Lock
        ‚Üì
Consensus / Moderation Phase
        ‚Üì
Technical Finalization Lock
        ‚Üì
Financial Envelope Opening (if staged)
        ‚Üì
Price Scoring Applied
        ‚Üì
Weighted Aggregation
        ‚Üì
Ranking Generated
        ‚Üì
Award Recommendation Report
```

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ CRITERIA STRUCTURE

Criteria are defined during procurement structuring (Logic 3) and cannot be changed after publication.

Example Weighted Model:

| Criterion         | Weight | Type                      |
| ----------------- | ------ | ------------------------- |
| Technical Quality | 40%    | Manual scoring            |
| Price             | 35%    | Automated formula         |
| Delivery Timeline | 10%    | Formula                   |
| Experience        | 10%    | Manual + documented proof |
| Risk Profile      | 5%     | Automated                 |

System enforces:

* Total weight = 100%
* No hidden criteria
* No post-opening modification

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ TYPES OF SCORING MECHANISMS

---

## üîπ A. Automated Formula-Based Scoring (Objective)

Used for:

* Price comparison
* Delivery time comparison
* Quantitative metrics

Example (Lowest Price Formula):

```
Price Score = (Lowest Bid / Bid Price) √ó Maximum Price Points
```

Example (Delivery Time Formula):

```
Delivery Score = (Shortest Delivery / Bid Delivery) √ó Points
```

These are calculated automatically by system.

---

## üîπ B. Manual Scoring (Subject-Matter Judgment)

Used for:

* Methodology quality
* Team expertise
* Innovation
* Technical compliance

Controls:

* Predefined scoring rubric
* Numeric scale (e.g., 0‚Äì10)
* Mandatory justification text
* Reference to evidence

---

## üîπ C. Binary Compliance Checks

Used for:

* Mandatory certifications
* Legal eligibility
* Required documents

If non-compliant:

* Automatic disqualification
* Or zero score for that criterion

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ INDIVIDUAL SCORING PHASE

Each evaluator:

* Scores independently
* Cannot see others‚Äô scores initially
* Must provide justification for non-maximum or low scores

System logs:

* Timestamp
* Score given
* Comments entered
* IP address

Prevents group bias.

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ SCORE LOCKING MECHANISM

Once evaluator submits score:

* Score becomes immutable
* Cannot be edited without formal revision workflow
* Any revision requires:

  * Justification
  * Audit log entry
  * Approval (if policy requires)

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ CONSENSUS / MODERATION PHASE

After individual scoring:

```
All Scores Submitted
        ‚Üì
System Displays Score Spread
        ‚Üì
Outlier Detection Triggered
        ‚Üì
Committee Discussion
        ‚Üì
Optional Moderated Adjustment
        ‚Üì
Final Technical Score Locked
```

Outlier logic example:

```
If Score Deviation > 30% from Mean
Flag as Outlier
```

Moderation must:

* Record reason
* Record participants
* Be time-stamped

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ FINANCIAL SCORING PHASE

After technical phase locked:

* Financial envelopes decrypted (Logic 7)
* Price scoring formula applied automatically
* No manual override allowed (unless policy defined)

System ensures:

* Technical score cannot be changed post-financial opening.

---

# üîü WEIGHTED AGGREGATION ENGINE

Final score calculation:

```
Final Score =
(Technical Score √ó Technical Weight)
+ (Price Score √ó Price Weight)
+ (Other Criteria √ó Their Weights)
```

System produces:

* Raw score per criterion
* Weighted score
* Final aggregate score
* Ranking order

No manual re-ranking allowed without override protocol.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ RISK-ADJUSTED SCORING (Optional Advanced Layer)

System may include:

* Risk penalty factor (from Logic 1)
* Past performance adjustment
* Dispute frequency modifier

Example:

```
Adjusted Score = Final Score ‚àí Risk Penalty
```

Must be predefined before tender publication.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ DISQUALIFICATION LOGIC

Automatic triggers:

* Missing mandatory document
* Non-compliant technical requirement
* Arithmetic error beyond threshold
* Conflict of interest discovered

System logs reason and prevents further scoring.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ COMPARATIVE ANALYSIS DASHBOARD

Evaluation interface includes:

* Side-by-side comparison
* Score breakdown by criterion
* Variance analysis
* Financial deviation analysis
* Risk indicator display

No hidden scoring fields.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ JUSTIFICATION & DEFENSIBILITY CONTROLS

For each bid:

System generates:

* Score summary
* Individual evaluator comments
* Consensus explanation
* Final ranking rationale
* Compliance confirmation

This becomes the official evaluation report.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ BIAS & MANIPULATION PREVENTION CONTROLS

System prevents:

‚ùå Changing weights after opening
‚ùå Editing scores without trace
‚ùå Viewing financial bids early
‚ùå Evaluator seeing supplier identity (if blind mode enabled)
‚ùå Single-person award authority

Optional blind evaluation:

* Supplier identity hidden during technical scoring.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ DATA MODEL STRUCTURE

Core Tables:

* Evaluation_Criteria
* Evaluator_Assignments
* Individual_Scores
* Score_Justifications
* Moderation_Log
* Final_Scores
* Disqualification_Log
